The paper focuses on developing a system for end-user creation of robust task plans for collaborative robots, which involves integrating perception, spatial reasoning, and robot actions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper heavily relies on computer vision techniques such as object segmentation and pose estimation, indicating that it may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also emphasizes the importance of creating a system that is easy for non-experts to use, which suggests that it may belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the system on multiple industrial robots, indicating that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
